{{afc comment|Wikidata entry (none) Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 07:41, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Shrine | name = {{ill|Kotoshironushi Shrine|ja|事代主神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi Shrine|qq=}} | image = [[File:IMG_nitakubi.JPG|250px]] | location = [[:en:Shin-Kamigotō|Shinkamigotō, Nagasaki]], [[:en:Nagasaki Prefecture|Nagasaki Prefecture]], Nitakubi 806 | coordinates = {{coord|33|01|08.4|N|129|05|29.8|E|scale:25000|name=Kotoshironushi Shrine}} | deity = {{ill|Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 事代主}} and three other deities | status = Former Village shrine | established = Bunmei 15 (1483) | main_hall = | festival = October 19 | rituals = {{ill|Kamigoto Kagura|ja|上五島神楽|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamigoto Kagura|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Gion Festival, Annual Grand Festival) }}
'''{{ill|Kotoshironushi Shrine|ja|事代主神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi Shrine|qq=}}''' (ことしろぬしじんじゃ) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in {{ill|Nitakubi|ja|似首郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nitakubi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, [[:en:Shin-Kamigotō|Shinkamigotō, Nagasaki]], [[:en:Nagasaki Prefecture|Nagasaki Prefecture]].
== Enshrined Deities == The shrine enshrines four deities: * {{ill|Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 事代主}} * {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大国主}} * {{ill|Susanoo|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素戔男神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} * [[:en:Ōmononushi|Ōmononushi]] (worshiped as [[Konpira Gongen|Konpira]])
Among them, {{ill|Susanoo|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素戔男神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} was enshrined following the merger with [[:en:Yasaka Shrine|Yasaka Shrine]].
== History == [[File:IMG_nitakubi2.JPG|170px|thumb|Worship Hall]] [[File:IMG_nitakubi1.JPG|170px|thumb|Ebisu Shrine]]
The shrine was founded in Bunmei 15 (1483) on September 15. Historically, the region has practiced {{ill|phallus worship|ja|性器崇拝|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/phallus worship|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 生殖器崇拝}}, with tall, protruding rocks resembling male genitalia considered sacred. Behind the shrine, {{ill|Ebisu Shrine|ja|恵美須神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ebisu Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to えびす神社}} enshrines stones shaped like male genitalia.
In Meiwa 8 (1771), the shrine buildings were rebuilt, and {{ill|Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 事代主}} (worshipped as {{ill|Ebisu|ja|恵美須神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ebisu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) was invited from [[:en:Nishinomiya Shrine|Nishinomiya Shrine]] in [[:en:Settsu Province|Settsu Province]]. The shrine likely adopted the name {{ill|Ebisu Shrine|ja|恵美須神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ebisu Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to えびす神社}} around this time. The shrine buildings were washed away by waves in Bunka 3 (1806), later rebuilt, but burned down in Bunkyū 1 (1862).
In Meiji 3 (1870), the shrine was renamed Kotoshironushi Shrine. In Meiji 7 (1874), it was designated as a {{ill|village shrine|ja|村社|lt=Son-sha|1=Modern_system_of_ranked_Shinto_shrines#Village_shrines|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/village shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度}}. In Meiji 41 (1908), it merged with Yasaka Shrine. The shrine burned down again in Shōwa 8 (1933), but was designated as a {{ill|Shinsen Heihaku-ryō Kyōshin Shrine|ja|神饌幣帛料供進神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinsen Heihaku-ryō Kyōshin Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in Shōwa 9 (1934).
== Festivals == The [[:en:Gion Matsuri|Gion Festival]] and the annual festival on October 18–19 feature performances of {{ill|Kamigoto Kagura|ja|上五島神楽|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamigoto Kagura|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. This kagura was designated as an {{ill|Intangible Folk Cultural Property of Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Intangible Folk Cultural Property of Nagasaki Prefecture|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 民俗文化財}} in 1981 and later as a national {{ill|Intangible Folk Cultural Properties Requiring Documentation|lt=Intangible Folk Cultural Properties Requiring Documentation|lt=Selected Intangible Folk Cultural Property|ja|選択無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Selected Intangible Folk Cultural Property|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 記録作成等の措置を講ずべき無形の民俗文化財}} in 2002.<ref>[https://bunka.nii.ac.jp/heritages/detail/137114 Cultural Heritage Online]</ref> In 2016, it was designated as an {{ill|Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property|ja|重要無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property|qq=}} of Japan.<ref>[http://www.pref.nagasaki.jp/bunkadb/index.php/view/459 Nagasaki Prefecture Cultural Properties]</ref>
;Major Festivals and Rituals * {{ill|Gantan-sai (New Year's Festival)|ja|元旦祭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gantan-sai (New Year's Festival)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 歳旦祭}} (January) * Dragon God Festival (March) * {{ill|Water God Festival|ja|水神祭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Water God Festival|qq=}} (April) * Nagoshi Festival (June) * [[:en:Gion Matsuri|Gion Festival]] (July) * {{ill|Reisai|fr|Reisai|lt=Annual Grand Festival|ja|例大祭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Reisai|qq=|ja_comment=fixed the redirect|1=Reisai|2=ja|3=例祭|4=fr|5=Reisai|lt=Reitaisai}} (October 18–19) * {{ill|Shichi-Go-San Festival|ja|七五三祭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shichi-Go-San Festival|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (November) * {{ill|Ōharae (Great Purification Ceremony)|ja|大祓式|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōharae (Great Purification Ceremony)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大祓}} (December)
